## How each requirement is met

| # | Requirement | Implementation |
|---|-------------|----------------|
| 1 | Search input at the top | Controlled `<input type="search">` bound to `inputValue` |
| 2 | Custom 300 ms debounce, no lodash | `useDebounce` hook — `useState` + `useEffect` + `setTimeout` |
| 3 | Case-insensitive substring match on `name` | `item.name.toLowerCase().includes(activeQuery.toLowerCase())` |
| 4 | "Searching…" during debounce delay | `isSearching = isPending && !inputIsEmpty` guards the indicator |
| 5 | Empty input → show all | `activeQuery === ''` short-circuits the filter to return `ITEMS` |
| 6 | Highlight matches with `<mark>` | `highlightMatch` splits via a **capturing-group regex** — matched parts land at odd indices and get wrapped |
| 7 | "No results found" | Rendered when `!isSearching && filteredItems.length === 0` |
| 8 | Cleanup on unmount | `return () => clearTimeout(timerId)` in `useEffect` — fires on unmount **and** on every value change (cancels the previous timer) |
| 9 | Whitespace-only = empty; special chars safe | `inputIsEmpty = inputValue.trim() === ''` snaps to empty immediately; `escapeRegex` neutralises all regex metacharacters before they enter `RegExp` |

### Key design decisions

- **Whitespace clears immediately** — `inputIsEmpty` is checked against the *raw* input, not the debounced value, so clearing the field restores all items in the same render cycle rather than after a 300 ms wait.
- **`highlightMatch` uses `split` with a capturing group** — this is the idiomatic, `lastIndex`-safe way to interleave text nodes and `<mark>` elements without running the regex twice.
- **`isSearching` guards the "No results" message** — prevents a flash of "No results" for the *previous* query while the next one is still debouncing.

